reviews.review_description:
I had been looking forward to this one since it was first announced, and bought it day one.  As a fan of Green Hell and other Survival games, I thought this looked like a no brainer.  After loading in to play, despite the appearance of the game in no way suggestive of a Quest 3 exclusive and finding the game mechanics to lack any real depth, I was still able to enjoy my time playing.  During my sessions, I would encounter little bugs here and there, nothing game breaking, but as my in game time progressed, the bugs began piling up to the point where the game is truly broken and I am unable to progress.  

A brief list:  
I am unable to craft new ammunition;  
I am unable to reload my guns; 
My bullets go right through enemies without causing damage and I too, can not be shot; 
I can not retrieve items from my backpack nor can I remove my knife from it’s sheath.; 
I fall through floors when dismounting ladders; 
my gun disappears from my backpack.  

They just released the first (11gb!) patch but sadly none of the issues plaguing me were addressed.  I had been affected by my thirst and hunger levels not decreasing, and they fixed that, and they removed the ability to use harmful food items to pay for fast travel (which was an exploit I actually enjoyed) but my game remains broken, which is very frustrating after investing 15+hours.  

When/If these issues are addressed, I will adjust my review accordingly, but I am fed up with incomplete/bug ridden games being released turning us into unwitting beta testers.  Would also be very happy to see them either add more phrases for NPC’s to utter, or have them speak far less often.  As it stands, they repeat the same 4 or 5 lines constantly during a firefight and you’ll be sick of them before completing your first altercation.

UPDATE:  I’ve changed my review from one star to three.   I was able to brute force my way through and have since completed the game.  All in all , I enjoyed my time with Tracked: Shoot to Survive.  Also, the devs have contacted me in order to resolve the bugs I experienced.  My remaining concerns:  

1. The graphics do not seem to be taking advantage of the Quest 3’s ability.
2.  Game breaking  bugs should have been ironed out before release.
3.  It seems as though there was more planned for this game and it got scaled back.  For instance, the inclusion of the mining mechanic- which I never had to use.
4.  Without going into spoilers, I found the story to be a little far fetched in as much as the college kid who didn’t like to hunt is now essentially become Rambo.

However, as I said, I did enjoy my time playing and played to completion- which I can’t say for a lot of games I own.
